Work individually or with a partner to complete the following user story:

* As a participant, I want to get started with Hybrid Edge Cloud (HEC) and understand how to utilize edgeEngine.

## Acceptance Criteria

* It's done when you have successfully set up and understood the basic concepts of HEC and edgeEngine.

## 📝 Instructions

1. Review the introduction to Hybrid Edge Cloud (HEC) provided in the course material.
2. Understand the key concepts and components of HEC, including edgeEngine.
3. Follow the step-by-step guide to set up edgeEngine on your development environment.
4. Experiment with basic commands or operations related to edgeEngine.
5. Validate the setup by running a sample project or test provided in the course material.

## 📝 Resources

- [Link to Introduction to HEC](#)
- [Link to edgeEngine Setup Guide](#)
- [Link to Sample Project or Test](#)

## 💡 Hints

- Pay attention to any prerequisites or system requirements for setting up edgeEngine.
- Reach out to your instructor or peers if you encounter any challenges during the setup process.

## 🏆 Bonus

If you have completed this activity, consider the following challenge to further your knowledge:

* Explore advanced features or capabilities of edgeEngine.
* Document your findings and share them with your peers or instructor.

## 📝 Notes

Getting started with HEC and edgeEngine is a foundational step in understanding edge computing and developing edge-enabled applications.

